      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Mitsuhide",
          "speakerSide": "left",
          "portraitKey": "mitsuhide_calm",
          "text": "They have chosen the ground well.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Nobunaga",
          "speakerSide": "right",
          "portraitKey": "nobunaga_fierce",
          "text": "They always do. We have to take this crossing anyway.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S09_WIN",
      "backgroundKey": "nagashima_crossing_aftermath",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_victory_somber",
      "sceneOrder": 17,
      "nextSceneRef": "S10",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The crossing falls by midday. The Ikko-ikki retreat into the marshlands — intact, orderly, taking their wounded. They were not broken. But the road is open.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "Mitsuhide surveys the crossing without speaking. Then, quietly, to no one in particular:",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Mitsuhide",
          "speakerSide": "left",
          "portraitKey": "mitsuhide_calm",
          "text": "Gyokan would have said the road being open is its own kind of text. Something written in the right medium, for the right reader.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Nobunaga",
          "speakerSide": "right",
          "portraitKey": "nobunaga_cold",
          "text": "He taught you well.",
          "lineOrder": 4
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "Mitsuhide says nothing further. He goes back to work. The pressure that was in the room before the battle is, for now, somewhere else.",
          "lineOrder": 5
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S09_WIN_COLD",
      "backgroundKey": "nagashima_crossing_aftermath",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_victory_somber",
      "sceneOrder": 17,
      "isConditionalVariant": true,
      "conditionalVariantOf": "S09_WIN",
      "nextSceneRef": "S10",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "flagCondition": {
        "flagKey": "mitsuhide_loyalty",
        "operator": "lte",
        "value": 0
      },
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The crossing falls by midday. The Ikko-ikki retreat intact. The road is open.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "Mitsuhide is already at the next marker on the map before Nobunaga reaches the bank. There is no pause. There is no ceremony. The work continues.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The silence between them is not the silence of men who have understood each other. It is the silence of men who have stopped trying.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S10",
      "backgroundKey": "gifu_castle_map_room_day",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_quiet_resolve",
      "sceneOrder": 19,
      "nextSceneRef": null,
      "routingMode": "choices",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "A courier arrives from Katsuie's camp the morning after the crossing. No letter. A short sword in a plain wooden case — campaign steel, utilitarian, the kind of blade a general actually carries rather than displays. A note in Katsuie's handwriting, four words: 'The road stays open.'",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Mitsuhide",
          "speakerSide": "left",
          "portraitKey": "mitsuhide_calm",
          "text": "He does not usually send gifts.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Nobunaga",
          "speakerSide": "right",
          "portraitKey": "nobunaga_cold",
          "text": "This isn't a gift. It's an acknowledgment. There's a difference.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        }
      ],
      "choices": [
        {
          "choiceText": "Accept it. Send back a reply: 'As it always will.'",
          "nextSceneRef": "S10A",
          "flagKey": "weapon_legacy",
          "flagValue": 1,
          "flagKey2": "katsuie_loyalty",
          "flagValue2": 1,
          "choiceOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "choiceText": "Return it with a note: a general's blade belongs in the field, not on a lord's table.",
          "nextSceneRef": "S10B",
          "flagKey": "katsuie_loyalty",
          "flagValue": 1,
          "flagKey2": null,
          "flagValue2": null,
          "choiceOrder": 2
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S10A",
      "backgroundKey": "gifu_castle_map_room_day",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_quiet_resolve",
      "sceneOrder": 20,
      "nextSceneRef": "S11_WIN",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The reply goes back the same day. Katsuie receives it at the northern wall. He reads it once, folds it once, and puts it in his armour. He does not mention it again. Neither does Nobunaga. The blade sits on the corner of the campaign table for the rest of the chapter, and nobody moves it.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S10B",
      "backgroundKey": "gifu_castle_map_room_day",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_quiet_resolve",
      "sceneOrder": 21,
      "nextSceneRef": "S11_WIN",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The blade goes back the same day with the note. Katsuie receives it at the northern wall. He reads the note. He buckles the sword back on without a word to anyone. It is a clean answer. He respects clean answers.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S09_LOSE",
      "backgroundKey": "nagashima_retreat_night",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_defeat",
      "sceneOrder": 22,
      "nextSceneRef": "S11_LOSE",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The assault fails. The marshland swallows the advance and spits it back out. You retreat in order — which is itself a skill — but the crossing holds for the monks.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Mitsuhide",
          "speakerSide": "left",
          "portraitKey": "mitsuhide_grim",
          "text": "Different season. Different approach. The crossing will fall. Just not today.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "He says it standing beside Nobunaga at the retreat line. Not to the map. To him. The difference is not small.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S09_LOSE_COLD",
      "backgroundKey": "nagashima_retreat_night",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_defeat",
      "sceneOrder": 22,
      "isConditionalVariant": true,
      "conditionalVariantOf": "S09_LOSE",
      "nextSceneRef": "S11_LOSE",
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": false,
      "flagCondition": {
        "flagKey": "mitsuhide_loyalty",
        "operator": "lte",
        "value": 0
      },
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "The assault fails. You retreat in order. The crossing holds for the monks.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "Mitsuhide states the tactical position to the assembled captains. His voice is precise. He does not look at Nobunaga while he speaks.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Mitsuhide",
          "speakerSide": "left",
          "portraitKey": "mitsuhide_grim",
          "text": "Different season. Different approach. The crossing will fall.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "He says it to the room. Not to his lord. That is the thing that has changed, and only Nobunaga is close enough to notice.",
          "lineOrder": 4
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S11_WIN",
      "backgroundKey": "gifu_castle_tower_night",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_tension_resolve",
      "sceneOrder": 24,
      "nextSceneRef": null,
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": true,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "A letter arrives from Kennyo. Formal. Precise. It does not mention the outpost or the crossing. It mentions only that the Honganji will endure.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Nobunaga",
          "speakerSide": "right",
          "portraitKey": "nobunaga_cold",
          "text": "He's patient. Good. Patient men telegraph their patience. I'll see him coming long before he arrives.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "Somewhere in Osaka, Kennyo folds his own copy of the letter. He does not smile. He begins the long game.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    },
    {
      "sceneRef": "S11_LOSE",
      "backgroundKey": "gifu_castle_tower_night",
      "bgmKey": "bgm_defeat",
      "sceneOrder": 25,
      "nextSceneRef": null,
      "isBattleGate": false,
      "isChapterEnd": true,
      "dialogueLines": [
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "A letter arrives from Kennyo. Formal. Precise. It mentions, in passing, that the Nagashima crossing remains open to Honganji pilgrims. It does not need to say anything else.",
          "lineOrder": 1
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Nobunaga",
          "speakerSide": "right",
          "portraitKey": "nobunaga_cold",
          "text": "He's patient. And now he knows I know it.",
          "lineOrder": 2
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Narrator",
          "speakerSide": "none",
          "portraitKey": null,
          "text": "Somewhere in Osaka, Kennyo reads a report from the delta. He permits himself one moment of satisfaction. Then he begins the next stage of the long game, which is now measurably longer than it was this morning.",
          "lineOrder": 3
        },
        {
          "speakerName": "Nobunaga",
          "speakerSide": "right",
          "portraitKey": "nobunaga_cold",
          "text": "The crossing falls next time. I have seen the ground now. That was worth the cost of today.",
          "lineOrder": 4
        }
      ],
      "choices": []
    }
  ]
}
